Package org.ivoa.dm.uws

Class Parameter

java.lang.Object
org.ivoa.dm.uws.Parameter
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations, org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<String>
@Entity @VoDml(id="uws:Parameter", role=objectType) public class Parameter extends Object implements org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulationsForObjectType<String>
the list of input parameters to the job - if the job description language does not naturally have parameters, then this list should contain one element which is the content of the original POST that created the job. objectType: Parameter

  • Field Details

    • byReference

      @VoDml(id="uws:Parameter.byReference", role=attribute, type="ivoa:boolean", typeRole=primitiveType) protected Boolean byReference
      if this attribute is true then the content of the parameter represents a URL to retrieve the actual parameter value. It is up to the implementation to decide if a parameter value cannot be returned directly as the content - the basic rule is that the representation of the parameter must allow the whole job element to be valid XML. If this cannot be achieved then the parameter value must be returned by reference. : Attribute byReference : multiplicity 1

    • id

      @VoDml(id="uws:Parameter.id", role=attribute, type="ivoa:string", typeRole=primitiveType) protected String id
      the identifier for the parameter . : Attribute id : multiplicity 1

    • isPost

      @VoDml(id="uws:Parameter.isPost", role=attribute, type="ivoa:boolean", typeRole=primitiveType) protected Boolean isPost
      is the original job creation post simply an opaque post that cannot be easily fitted into the parameter model, then a single 'parameter' description should be returned with this set to true. : Attribute isPost : multiplicity 1

    • Parameter

      public Parameter(Boolean byReference, String id, Boolean isPost)
      full parameter constructor.
      Parameters:
      byReference - if this attribute is true then the content of the parameter represents a URL to retrieve the actual parameter value. It is up to the implementation to decide if a parameter value cannot be returned directly as the content - the basic rule is that the representation of the parameter must allow the whole job element to be valid XML. If this cannot be achieved then the parameter value must be returned by reference.
      id - the identifier for the parameter .
      isPost - is the original job creation post simply an opaque post that cannot be easily fitted into the parameter model, then a single 'parameter' description should be returned with this set to true.
